%N A005618 a(n) = 6*a(n-1) - 8, with a(0) = 4.
%C A005618 Number of functions expressible by width-2 ordered binary decision diagrams on n+1 variables in a fixed order. - _Kiran Tomlinson_, Apr 15 2026
%D A005618 N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
%H A005618 J. T. Butler, <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20240413195017/http://faculty.nps.edu/butler/PDF/1978/But_IEEETC1978.pdf">Tandem networks of universal cells</a>, IEEE Trans. Computers, C-27 (1978), 785-799. (<a href="/A005618/a005618.pdf">Annotated scanned copy</a>)
%H A005618 K. K. Maitra, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1109/TEC.1962.5219346">Cascaded switching networks of two-input flexible cells</a>, IEEE Trans. Electron. Computers, C-11 (1962), 136-143.
%H A005618 Simon Plouffe, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/0911.4975">Approximations de séries génératrices et quelques conjectures</a>, Dissertation, Université du Québec à Montréal, 1992; arXiv:0911.4975 [math.NT], 2009.
%H A005618 Simon Plouffe, <a href="/A000051/a000051_2.pdf">1031 Generating Functions</a>, Appendix to Thesis, Montreal, 1992
%H A005618 <a href="/index/Rec#order_02">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (7,-6).
%F A005618 G.f.: ( 4-12*x ) / ( (6*x-1)*(x-1) ). - _Simon Plouffe_ in his 1992 dissertation
%F A005618 For n > 0, a(n) = N(n,2,2) where N(n,s,r) is defined in A005608. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jul 13 2016
%F A005618 a(n) = 4 * A261399(n+1) = (12*6^n+8)/5. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Apr 15 2026
%F A005618 E.g.f.: 4*exp(x)*(2 + 3*exp(5*x))/5. - _Stefano Spezia_, Apr 26 2026
